				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard vs Enchanter...<a name="50338"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 6 04 2:34 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The obvious thing to worry about is his debuffs. Tash is going to really hurt. Don't know if hed be chain nuking you, but you can bet he'll have his pet up. 
<br />

<br />
Have your ancient mezz?
<br />

<br />
I'd go in with pumices and dispell him a couple times with a pumice and disillusionment. Then slap ancient mezz on him and drain mana. His mana regen is going to be crappy with only FT, should buy you some time once he is dry. His runes are going to make it hard to damage him though. I'd go with chants, his MR is high, what about disease/poison/elementals?
<br />

<br />
Chain mezzing with melee might be your best/only chance from what I see.
<br />

<br />
Expect to be tashed then chain stunned while their pet beats you to death or some similar strategy of keeping you locked down.
<br />

<br />
I'm not familiar with end game enchanters though, they have many tricks from what I have seen of them soloing and grouping.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=844375">Reilna Voiceofwar</A><br>

