			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard vs Enchanter...<a name="50399"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 6 04 7:42 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Since you are from a PvP server, I doubt many of us from blue servers can offer you much helpful advice. I would want to get my MR as high as possible BEFORE PoV. That way when he strips buffs he will still have a hard time landing anything on you.
<br />

<br />
If it were me, I would DOT myself for the start of the fight. Then I would cure him to take care of the potential for a crimson potion. Then I would mez him with ancient mez and drain all his mana. I really don't worry much about a chanter pet. I would just stay out of its way while killing it with Saryns and keeping the enchanter mezzed. You can cure tash if you are worried about it. But once the chanter is drained of all mana, I am not sure that being tashed matters at all. Once he is drained of mana then strip away all his buffs, while stunning (bellow), interupting (Saryns) and meleeing him down. Or just chant/Saryns him down.
<br />

<br />
The real danger here is that his ancient mez (assuming he has it) has a faster cast time than bard ancient mez. If he gets you mezzed first, then he has a good chance of winning unless he makes a mistake. If you can keep yourself dotted so that his mez is broken if he lands it then you have an advantage. As I recall, his ancient mez has a much longer refresh time than a bard's ancient mez.
<br />

<br />
Let us know how it goes.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Drumm
<br />
65 Bard
<br />
Torv Server</span></td>
