				<td colspan="2"><span>What you got here basically is the 2 most versatile classes having a go at each other. 
<br />
I've never done any pvp on my bard but I did take a few names with the enchanter. 
<br />
I never got to kill a bard though, but never been killed by one either. We kinda gave up on the fight and joined forces on a stack of minotaur hero brew ( we were the last 2 standing in an arena FFA heheh, noone saw the invis gnome in the corner<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-10.gif" border="0" alt="Blushing" hspace="2" /><img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />)
<br />

<br />
Keep in mind that in the end it boils down to the skill of the player and not the capabilities of the class.
<br />
(Like knowing that my runes will mitigate your melee damage but your dotsongs will bypass the friggin things /boggle)
<br />

<br />
Spell line up:
<br />

<br />
- Tash (duh)
<br />
- Ancient rapture
<br />
- Forlorn deeds (debuff swap slot, once it's slowed, it's dead *grin*)
<br />
- Insanity (1100 pts nuke, without AA enhancers)
<br />
- swapslot (charm/extra nuke/manadrain ...)
<br />
- swapslot (initially Recant magic)
<br />
- Arcane Rune
<br />
- Rune of Zebuxurok
<br />

<br />
I'm assuming you get time to selfbuff before the fight. If not it's done in the first 54 seconds the opponent stands drooling I guess.
<br />

<br />
And then I usually wing it, no 2 fights are the same.
<br />
The chanter could charm something on you (if he's smart he'll take a mob you're kos to. Mez you, break charm and mez the pet, memblur mob and root both close to each other. Just make sure to finish off the player with a nuke to prevent exp loss)
<br />

<br />
Or when I really feel like rubbing it in, I'd try to melee the other person to death. (chanters can tank a slowed mob fine alternating runes)
<br />

<br />
A hasted and NDT'd enchanter with maxxed piercing wielding Silver Dagger of Destruction is no joke (even if it sounds like one /giggle). I will keep using my rightclick dispell and blind during that mayhem.
<br />
